Introduction: "The virus belongs to the incubation period, we have to do all the preparation, loss of money to do. "

By Liu Jia

On New Year's Day twenty-seven, Liao Jiaming, who had just returned from Chengdu to his home province of Jiangxi to prepare for the Spring Festival, hurriedly bought a plane ticket to fly back to Chengdu the next day. There is only one reason for it -- a "productive mask" .

By Liu Jia

On New Year's Day twenty-seven, Liao Jiaming, who had just returned from Chengdu to his home province of Jiangxi to prepare for the Spring Festival, hurriedly bought a plane ticket to fly back to Chengdu the next day. There is only one reason for it -- a "productive mask" .

He is the general manager of Sichuan Hengming Medical Equipment Co. , Ltd (hereinafter referred to as "Hengming Medical") , one of the many automated production lines for medical devices at the company's Pengzhou factory in Chengdu.

Masks are the first barrier to prevent the spread of COVID-19. On the night of his decision to return to Chengdu, Liao contacted the factory director and called the workers one by one, promising to reimburse them for the bus fare and tripling their wages to try to keep the production line running 24 hours a day during the holiday.

The first batch of medical masks, surgical clothes, protective caps and other medical materials in the emergency disinfection analysis completed, Hang Ming medical decided to donate aid to Wuhan. In addition, Hang Ming Medical, which used to be sold only offline, launched online for the first time on tmall during the Spring Festival, and sold out of 100,000 disposable surgical masks that went online in one morning. At present, Hengming medical products are subject to the unified deployment of relevant government departments, some of the materials directly to the hospital, the first-line law enforcement personnel.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Liao Jiaming told China business news that the factory currently operates on three shifts, but the daily production of masks fluctuates considerably, from about 20,000 to about 80,000. The reason behind the output fluctuation lies in the overspeed of the machine and the supply of raw materials.

Because the machine that produces the mask is in 24-hour overspeed operation, the machine occasionally appears the problem which the ordinary worker can not solve, so each shift sends a technician to guard the machine in front, once the machine has the problem to deal with immediately.

Out of judgment of the epidemic situation, Hang Ming medical decided to continue to purchase machines and add more production lines, but unexpectedly, the mask machine also rose in price. The purchase price of a mask-making machine was around 180,000, now it is around 60,000 in two days. "Two days ago, we ordered two masks and raised them to 240,000. Today, we have 290,000 and 300,000. "

In addition to machine maintenance and procurement costs, the factory also faces difficulties in the supply of raw materials. From the spunbonded nonwovens for the face layer of the mask to the melt-blown nonwovens for the core part of the mask, and then to the nose clip and the Lanyard, there are various degrees of shortages and rising costs. Liao said that during the Spring Festival, the overall price of raw materials for face masks rose by about 50 percent, and is still rising every day. However, there are also some suppliers who have the good faith to choose not to raise the price, or even lower the price of supply.

In fact, the mask profit is not big, special period plus labor costs, raw material costs, logistics costs, enterprise profit is further cut thin. Liao Jiaming said that the prices of the masks have not increased, and the supplies of the masks that have been deployed are currently supplied free of charge. It is not necessary to calculate a certain loss of money. However, everyone is now focused on fighting the epidemic, "The virus is dormant, so we have to be fully prepared, even if we lose money. "

Unfortunately, due to the volatility of production and other multiple reasons, Hang Ming medical in tmall sales of some masks not shipped as scheduled, is facing many user complaints. According to Liao Jiaming estimate, because complain wait for a reason, only on-line platform calculates come down may want to pay a lot of compensation.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
However, today, Alibaba sources told reporters that the platform will communicate with businesses to verify and exempt them from responsibility for the priority supply of Wuhan anti-epidemic orders; consumers are pushing forward with the refund, there is a platform to pocket the bottom line.

In order to support and efficiently serve anti-epidemic enterprises in a timely manner, while the mask factory is busy in production, the local government department has sent a special working group to take a one-to-one service approach to enter the factory, to coordinate and solve the difficulties in the supply of raw materials, staff organization, logistics and transportation, and equipment procurement, and to help the enterprises to do a good job in the production of face masks and other emergency materials.

Liao Jiaming told the reporter that the relevant departments have sent a special team of four to six people to stay at the Hengming medical factory every day to help the enterprise solve problems encountered in the actual production, such as the shortage of raw materials, the government's factory teams help connect suppliers within and across provinces, reducing production worries. In particular, the government has learned that factories do not calculate the cost of procurement machinery to speed up the production of mask supplies, promised to find ways for enterprises to apply to make up the difference.

In addition, in the face of the capital turnover pressure of the factory to a certain extent, Liao Jiaming disclosed that the relevant personnel of the bank quickly learned the production and operation situation and financing needs of the enterprise on the spot, and formulated exclusive financial service plans for the enterprise on the spot, by granting special interest rates and waiving fees, Hang Ming's $1 million loan from the bank was disbursed within 48 hours.

At the end of the interview, Liao Jiaming told reporters that his family has 5 people, but only less than 10 masks in stock, only one person a day out for home shopping. The best protection for the average person, he urges, is to travel as little as possible; under tight supplies of masks, more protective gear can be set aside for front line workers.
